CodeClear.​NaturalDocs.​Engine.​Languages.​ParentElement
CodeClear.​NaturalDocs.​Engine.​Languages.​Element
public
CodeClear.​NaturalDocs.​Engine.​Languages.​ParentElement

A Element that also may contain child elements.  This is used not only for classes but for groups (so that settings may be inherited) and list topics and enums (to store embedded topics.)

Properties
IsRootElement
public bool IsRootElement { get; set }

Whether this element is intended to be the root for the file.

MaximumEffectiveChildAccessLevel
public AccessLevel MaximumEffectiveChildAccessLevel { get; set }

The maximum effective access level children can attain, which is usually the effective access level of the parent.  For example, a private class's children wolud have a maximum effective access level of private, even if they were declared public.  Will be AccessLevel.Unknown if it's not set.

DefaultDeclaredChildAccessLevel
public AccessLevel DefaultDeclaredChildAccessLevel { get; set }

The default declared access level of this element's children if not otherwise specified.  This can be greater than MaximumEffectiveChildAccessLevel because it's only the declared access level.  Will be AccessLevel.Unknown if it's not set.

DefaultChildLanguageID
public int DefaultChildLanguageID { get; set }

The language ID that applies to all children, or zero if it's not set.

DefaultChildClassString
public ClassString DefaultChildClassString { get; set }

The default ClassString all children should use, if set.  Use DefaultChildClassStringSet to see if this value is relevant, as null can be a valid value.  Setting this value will automatically set DefaultChildClassStringSet to true.

DefaultChildClassStringSet
public bool DefaultChildClassStringSet { get; set }

Whether <DeaultChildClassString> was set for this element, and thus whether its value is relevant.

ChildContextString
public ContextString ChildContextString { get; set }

The ContextString all children should use, if set.  Use ChildContextStringSet to see if this value is relevant, as null can be a valid value.  Setting this value will automatically set ChildContextStringSet to true.

ChildContextStringSet
public bool ChildContextStringSet { get; set }

Whether ChildContextString was set for this element, and thus whether its value is relevant.

EndingLineNumber
public int EndingLineNumber { get; set }

The line number where the parent's influence ends, or -1 if it hasn't been set yet.  The first line number is one, not zero.

EndingCharNumber
public int EndingCharNumber { get; set }

The character number where the parent's influence ends, or -1 if it hasn't been set yet.  The first character number is one, not zero, and is relative to the line, not the file.

EndingPosition
public Position EndingPosition { get; set }

The position where the parent's influence ends.
